            <!-- Maintenance Tips -->
            <div class="section">
                <h2>üîß October Maintenance Checklist</h2>
                <p>As the season winds down (or heats up for our southern friends), here are essential tasks for this month:</p>
                
                <div class="tips-list">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Winterization prep</strong> - For northern boaters: Schedule engine winterization by mid-November to beat the rush</li>
                        <li><strong>Inspect zincs</strong> - Replace if more than 50% deteriorated to protect underwater metals</li>
                        <li><strong>Battery maintenance</strong> - Clean terminals and check voltage; consider a battery tender for winter storage</li>
                        <li><strong>Canvas care</strong> - Clean and treat all canvas with marine-grade protectant before storage</li>
                        <li><strong>Bilge inspection</strong> - Check for any unusual water accumulation or oil residue</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Document everything with photos. This creates a maintenance history that increases resale value and helps you spot changes year over year.</p>
            </div>
            
